<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-3717] Support building aggregate javadoc for all project modules</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3717</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you run &quot;./gradlew javadoc&quot;, you will only get JavaDoc for the High Level Consumer. All the new clients are missing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://home.apache.org/~gwenshap/0.10.0.0-rc5/javadoc/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://home.apache.org/~gwenshap/0.10.0.0-rc5/javadoc/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suggest fixing in 0.10.0 branch and in trunk, not rolling a new release candidate, but updating our docs site.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
